One project that I'm very proud about that I think is very cool is GitHub health. If

00:12:13.659 --> 00:12:19.340
you have ever tried to get people to use GitHub in an organization, it is incredibly difficult.

00:12:19.340 --> 00:12:23.900
It's a steep learning curve and it's tough. The key thing about support is how do you

00:12:23.900 --> 00:12:28.780
go from a reactive support to a proactive support. So the question that we have tried

00:12:28.780 --> 00:12:34.340
to solve is can you proactively find studies that are struggling with GitHub and support

00:12:34.340 --> 00:12:38.820
them? And we can. There's a lot of different metrics and things that you can pull, like,

